      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Increases in the minimum wage can certainly impact small cafes by raising labor costs, which is a significant operational expense. To offset these higher costs, some businesses might need to slightly increase menu prices or become more efficient with staffing. Conversely, if demand remains high, the increased revenue could absorb some of the added labor expense. Ultimately, the impact depends heavily on your local market and pricing strategy.",
